Section 1:
1 L.D. 1307
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 LABOR
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 537, L.D. 1307, “An Act to Suspend the
10 Remittance Obligation for Paid Family and Medical Leave Private Plan Users”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Refund Premium Contributions Made by Employers with Approved
13 Private Plans to the Paid Family and Medical Leave Insurance Fund'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and before the
15 emergency clause and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. 26 MRSA §850-F, sub-§11 is enacted to read:
17 11. Refund of premium contributions. Premium contributions may be refunded
18 pursuant to this subsection.
19 A. An employer that remitted premium contributions to the fund on or after January 1,
20 2025 and that received approval to substitute a private plan pursuant to section 850-H
21 before January 1, 2026 is entitled to reimbursement of all premium contributions made
22 to the fund, together with any interest earned thereon, upon written request submitted
23 by mail to the department. Within 30 days of receipt of an employer's written request
24 for reimbursement of premium contributions under this paragraph, the department shall
25 refund the employer's premium contributions to the employer, together with any
26 interest earned thereon from the date of receipt of the request. For purposes of this
27 paragraph, an employer's request for reimbursement is deemed to be received by the
28 department on the date on which the employer's request for reimbursement was mailed
29 to the department.
30 B. An employer that elected to deduct any portion of its premium contribution from its
31 employees' wages as permitted by subsection 5 shall refund its employees for their
32 portion of premium contributions, together with any interest earned thereon, within 30
33 days of receipt of the refund from the department under paragraph A.
34 Sec. 2. Rules establishing expedited refund process and waiver of payroll
35 premiums by November 1, 2025. Pursuant to its rule-making authority under the
Page 1 - 132LR2176(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 537, L.D. 1307
316 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 26, section 850-Q, the Department of Labor shall amend
327 12-702 C.M.R. Chapter 1: Rules governing the Maine Paid Family and Medical Leave
338 Program to:
4 1. Implement a specified timeline for decisions on applications for substitution of
5 private plans that meet the requirements of Title 26, section 850-H, not to exceed 30 days
6 from the department's receipt of an employer's application for substitution of a private plan;
7 and
8 2. Conform to the provisions of Title 26, section 850-F, subsection 11 as provided in
9 this Act.
10 The rules must be in effect no later than November 1, 2025.
11 Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
12 allocations are made.
13 LABOR, DEPARTMENT OF
14 Paid Family and Medical Leave Insurance Fund Z383
15 Initiative: Allocates one-time funds for the cost to calculate and refund contributions paid
16 by employers that remitted premium contributions on or after January 1, 2025 and who
17 received approval to substitute a private plan before January 1, 2026.
18 PAID FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE 2025-26 2026-27
19 INSURANCE FUND
20 All Other $20,000 $0
21 __________ __________
22 PAID FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE $20,000 $0
23 INSURANCE FUND TOTAL
2148 '
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment is the minority report of the committee. This amendment changes the
2299 title and provides that an employer that remitted premium contributions to the Paid Family
3300 and Medical Leave Insurance Fund on or after January 1, 2025 and that received approval
3311 of a substitute private plan before January 1, 2026 is entitled to reimbursement of all
3322 premium contributions with interest. It requires the Department of Labor to refund the
3333 premium contributions within 30 days of receipt of request from the employer. It requires
3344 the employer to refund any premium contributions deducted from an employee within 30
3355 days if the employer deducted any portion of premium contributions under current law.
3366 The amendment requires the Department of Labor to update its rules relating to the paid
3377 family and medical leave benefits program. The amendment also adds an appropriations
3388 and allocations section.
3399 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
4400 (See attached)
